The title gives but arr approximate idea of the scope of the work. The collection of sources has ceased where Thucydides takes up his direct narrative, so that the quarrel which precipitated the Peloponnesian War has been excluded. An absolutely complete collection of passages bearing on the history of the Pentekontaetia would require many volumes, in which all the authorities should be printed irr full, and art, literature, and philosophy be represented along with politice and biography. In default of this, an attempt has been made to include such passages relating to the former matters as most directly concern history in the narrower sense of the word. Constitutional antiquities have been similarly dealt with, and from the side of historical development rather than with the object of describing the actual working of the constitution.
